text: All that we are is the result of what we have thought.
The same boiling water that softens the potato hardens the egg.
A problem well stated is a problem half-solved.
Your discipline is your destiny. Your limitations begin where your self-discipline ends.
Writing is the Geometry of the Soul.
Question with boldness even the existence of a God; because, if there be one, he must more approve of the homage of reason, than that of blind-folded fear.
Surround yourself with people who remind you more of the future than the past.
Whatever seems IN the way IS the way.
Share your knowledge. It is a way to achieve immortality.
Mediocrity is self-inflicted and genius is self-bestowed.
Learn like you’ll live forever.. live like you’ll die tomorrow.
The lips of Wisdom are closed, except to the ears of Understanding.
Philosopher > Initiate > Master
Iteration IS innovation.
Mind > Body > Soul
Knowledge > Experience > Wisdom
Thinking > Doing > Being
Success is the ability to go from failure to failure without a loss of enthusiasm.
notes: Widely attributed to Winston Churchill, but there is no evidence he said this.

text: It’s the mark of an educated mind to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it.
You don’t experience Life. You experience the Life you focus on.
The greatest illusion is that mankind has limitations.
To be great is to be misunderstood.
EGO: Edged God Out
You can either be a Host to God OR a hostage to your Ego.

I give thanks daily, not for mere riches, but for wisdom with which to recognize, embrace, and properly use the great abundance of riches I now have at my command. I have no enemies because I injure no man for any cause, but I try to benefit all with whom I come in contact, by teaching them the way to enduring riches. I have more material wealth than I need because I am free from greed and covet only the material things I can use while I live.
Everything is either an opportunity to grow or an obstacle to keep you from growing. You get to choose.
Chase the Goddess of Wisdom and the Goddess of Wealth will chase you.
Bliss = God talking to you

Our ordinary mind always tries to persuade us that we are nothing but acorns and that our greatest happiness will be to become bigger, fatter, shinier acorns; but that is of interest only to pigs. Our faith gives us knowledge of something better: that we can become oak trees.
Let me take you down, 'cause I'm going to. Strawberry fields. Nothing is real. And nothing to get hung about. Strawberry fields forever.
Science without religion is lame, religion without science is blind.
source: Science, Philosophy and Religion: A Symposium (1941)

text: I am blessed and highly favored - good things are supposed to happen to me!
Money finds me easily and frequently.
The greatest shortcoming of the human race is our inability to understand the exponential function.
I love us.
Integrity is the essence of everything successful.
The three most harmful addictions are heroin, carbohydrates, and a monthly salary.
It’s not worth an intelligent man’s time to be in the majority. By definition, there are already enough people to do that.
Be curious, not judgmental.
notes: Popularized by the show Ted Lasso, who attributes it to Whitman, though Whitman likely never said it.

text: Live life to the fullest. You have to color outside the lines once in a while if you want to make your life a masterpiece. Laugh some every day. Keep growing, keep dreaming, keep following your heart. The important thing is not to stop questioning.
notes: This is a pastiche of generic inspirational quotes incorrectly attributed to Einstein.

text: Truth is a pathless land.
The truth has zero maintenance costs.
Be a free thinker and don't accept everything you hear as truth. Be critical and evaluate what you believe in.
notes: Unlikely to be a genuine Aristotle quote.

text: Never doubt that a small group of thoughtful, committed citizens can change the world; indeed, it's the only thing that ever has.
Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.
source: Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith

text: It's easier to fool people than to convince them that they have been fooled.
The illiterate of the twenty-first century will not be those who cannot read and write, but those who cannot learn, unlearn, and relearn.
Great minds discuss ideas; average minds discuss events; small minds discuss people.
As the most intelligent form of life on this Earth, humans are the only ones that have to pay to live here. Does that not strike you as odd?
The only thing new in the world is the history you do not know.
I Am the universe.
I don’t have to believe everything I think.
Your birth and death happened at the same time.
Intellectuals solve problems, geniuses prevent them.
Broken crayons color as good as new ones.
Embrace the present moment with gratefulness and wonder, and you will turn it into whatever you have been waiting for.
A flower is simply a weed with a marketing budget.
Some men see things as they are and say, why; I dream things that never were and say, why not.
The quality of your mind determines the quality of your life.
There are millions of people who carry very toxic narratives in their mind and they call it 'my life'.

Man. Because he sacrifices his health in order to make money. Then he sacrifices money to recuperate his health. And then he is so anxious about the future that he does not enjoy the present; the result being that he does not live in the present or the future; he lives as if he is never going to die, and then dies having never really lived.
notes: Commonly attributed to the Dalai Lama, but likely written by James J. Lachard.

text: Would you rather be right or be happy?
Silence is the language of god, all else is poor translation.
The day science begins to study non-physical phenomena, it will make more progress in one decade than in all the previous centuries of its existence.
It is no measure of health to be well adjusted to a profoundly sick society.
The time to fix the roof is when the sun is shining.
Our infinite potential exists just on the other side of our discomfort zone.
Faith and Fear ask of you the same thing - to believe in something unseen.
Life isn't as serious as my mind makes it out to be.
The only thing that interferes with my learning is my education.
The ancestor of every action is a thought.
From the very forest itself comes the handle of the axe that fells it.
We are slaves to whatever we don’t understand.
What you resist persists, and that what you think about, you bring about.
The basis of life is absolute freedom. The objective of life is absolute joy. The result of life is absolute growth.

The purpose of life is to know and express Who You Are. If you do other than that during the days and times of your life, you will have not used those days and times in a way that profits your soul. It is soul profit we are after here, not body profit.
I completely trust my Infinite Self to do Anything in this lifetime.
Beliefs are the master plan used to create your reality.
Money can buy you a fine dog, but only love can make him wag his tail.
Miracles seldom occur in the lives of those who do not consider them possible.
The Lamps are different, but the LIGHT is the same.
I dwell in possibility.
Those who danced were thought insane by those who could not hear the music.
notes: Often attributed to Nietzsche, but the earliest source is Angela Monet.

text: Love is metaphysical gravity.
There are only two mistakes one can make along the road to truth; not going all the way, and not starting.

The great secret is a controlled imagination and a well-sustained attention firmly and repeatedly focused on the feeling of the wish fulfilled until it fills the mind and crowds all other ideas out of consciousness.
At the center of your being you have the answer; you know who you are and you know what you want.
You see, to go out of your mind, at least once a day, is tremendously important because by going out of your mind you will come to your senses.
We are not human beings having a spiritual experience. We are spiritual beings having a human experience.
Fall in love with your work, writing.
Religion is for people who are scared to go to hell. Spirituality is for people who have already been there.
notes: Often credited to Bonnie Raitt, but originally Vine Deloria Jr.

text: Science advances one death at a time.
In the age of information, ignorance is a choice.
The more you are willing to just let the world be something you’re aware of, the more it will let you be who you are— the awareness, the Self, the Atman, the Soul.
The opposite of a correct statement is a false statement. But the opposite of a profound truth may well be another profound truth.
I believe that banking institutions are more dangerous to our liberties than standing armies.
notes: This quote is widely considered spurious or misattributed.

text: The secret of change is to focus all of your energy, not on fighting the old, but on building the new.
notes: Often misattributed to the philosopher Socrates; it is from a character named Socrates in Dan Millman's book.

text: It's not what you look at that matters, it's what you see.
Your vision will become clear only when you look into your heart. Who looks outside, dreams. Who looks inside, awakens.
If you want to find the secrets of the universe, think in terms of energy, frequency and vibration.
If you only knew the magnificence of the 3, 6 and 9, then you would have the key to the universe.
If we have any pain in us at all, it means we have something to forgive.
Every great architect is - necessarily - a great poet. He must be a great original interpreter of his time, his day, his age.
An investment in knowledge always pays the best interest.
If you take your time, Deven, you'll have more of it.
Make Bliss my Life's Purpose.
It's not hard to make decisions when you know what your values are.
The Universe doesn't hear what you say, the Universe hears what you mean.
I AM the resurrection and the life in thought and feeling.
Man's concept of himself determines the world in which he lives.
Accept whatever comes to you woven in the pattern of your destiny, for what could more aptly fit your needs?
All riches have their origin in mind. Wealth is in ideas - not money.
If one advances confidently in the direction of his dreams, and endeavors to live the life which he has imagined, he will meet with a success unexpected in common hours.
The highest form of knowledge is to know who you are.
Forgiveness is the fragrance that the violet sheds on the heel that has crushed it.
If the highest aim of a captain were to preserve his ship, he would keep it in port forever.
I am whole, perfect, strong, powerful, loving, harmonious, prosperous and happy.
Manage your energy, not your time.
Have a Mind that is Open to Everything and Attached to Nothing.
notes: Often used by Wayne Dyer, but based on the teachings of Tilopa.

text: Change is inevitable but learning is optional.
You're only aware of the reality you choose to observe.
Nothing real can be threatened. Nothing unreal exists.
The world as you know it is a picture of your expectations.
Belief structures reality!
All The Truths of All the Worlds are written all around, and inside us. It only takes the eyes to see.
I hear and I forget. I see and I remember. I do and I understand.
Too many people spend money they haven't earned, to buy things they don't want, to impress people they don't like.
Practice not-doing and everything will fall into place.
Thought plus conviction equals manifestation.
There is no past or future. Using tenses to divide time is like making chalk marks on water.
Love is what we're born with, fear is what we learn here.
We are symbols and inhabit symbols.
Is it fair to have given us the memory of what was and the desire of what could be when we must suffer what is?
Let a hundred flowers bloom, let a hundred schools of thought contend.
source: Speech at the Supreme State Conference (May 2, 1956), though not published until 1957.

text: The reasonable man adapts himself to the world; the unreasonable one persists in trying to adapt the world to himself. Therefore all progress depends on the unreasonable man.
Reality is merely an illusion, albeit a very persistent one.
source: Attributed quote, often repeated in various publications

text: Where attention goes, energy flows; where intention goes, energy flows!
source: Secrets of the Millionaire Mind: Mastering the Inner Game of Wealth (2005)

text: When you change the way you look at things, the things you look at change.
source: Often attributed to Wayne Dyer; its original source is difficult to pinpoint but Dyer popularized it.

text: If you want to find the secrets of the universe, think in terms of energy, frequency and vibration.
source: Attributed quote, although its exact original source is debated. It reflects Tesla's general thinking and writings on physics and the universe.

text: As a species, we are in a constant state of amnesia.
source: War God: Nights of the Witch (2013)

text: Compound interest is the eighth wonder of the world. He who understands it, earns it ... he who doesn't ... pays it.
author_actual: Often attributed to Albert Einstein, but this is likely a misattribution.
source: The origin of this quote is uncertain. It's widely attributed to Albert Einstein, but there's no reliable evidence he said or wrote it. Some sources suggest it may have originated with others prior to Einstein.

text: I will be who I will be
A goal without a plan is just a wish.
source: Commonly attributed to Antoine de Saint-Exupéry, although a definitive source is difficult to pinpoint within his published works. It captures the sentiment found in his writings on action and purpose.

text: A master thinks only about what he intends to manifest.
source: Attributed to various self-help and new age sources; likely a modern paraphrase or synthesis of similar concepts.

text: Whether you think you can, or you think you can't – you're right.
source: Allegedly from his biography or various writings and speeches, though the exact origin is debated.

text: I am not what happened to me, I am what I choose to become.
source: Attributed, but difficult to verify exact original source. The sentiment aligns with Jungian psychology principles.

text: All our dreams can come true, if we have the courage to pursue them.
The highest form of ignorance is when you reject something you don't know anything about.
